JOHANNESBURG, May 24 – A toddler has been killed in a shack fire in the Benoni agricultural holdings, paramedics said on Thursday. ER24 spokesperson Annine Siddall said when paramedics arrived at around 7 am, they found that the boy had sustained fatal burn wounds. “Unfortunately, he was declared dead by ER24 medics in the room of the shack that caught alight. The toddler’s sister, a girl believed to be 12-years-old, did not sustain any injuries in the fire.” Local authorities will be investigating further. – African News Agency (ANA)